30/10/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Council of Europe (CoE) Secretary-General Terry Davis wrapped up a two-day visit to BiH on Tuesday (October 30th).
On Monday, he met with the three members of the BiH presidency, reminding them that the country still has certain obligations to fulfil as a CoE member.
In particular, officials agreed on the need to strengthen the rights of national minorities and to implement reforms related to higher education.
Davis met with Foreign Minister Sven Alkalaj, and addresses both chambers of parliament Tuesday.
In other news, High Representative Miroslav Lajcak met on Monday with NATO's deputy supreme allied commander for Europe and the EU's operation commander for Althea, General John McColl.
Officials discussed the latest developments in the country and EUFOR's role in preserving security throughout BiH, in accordance with its Dayton Accord-derived mandate.
(Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 30/10/07;
Fena, RTRS, OHR website - 29/10/07)
